summary:
Because I believe that interior architecture is a tool to improve people's well-being and because I have the necessary knowledge to enhance creativity, productivity and happiness through design, I have focused on Learning Spaces.

In 2015, after 10 years of working as an architect, I started ğ—¦ğ—§ğ—¨ğ——ğ—œğ—¢ ğ— ğ—”ğ—§ğ—œğ—§ğ—”, and since then, I have carried out various interior design projects ranging from domestic, hospitality and of course, spaces for creativity. This experience has nurtured 5 years of teaching in design workshops in schools and universities.

I am working as a solopreneur and I am enthusiastic to collaborate with different professionals, individuals, projects and scenarios.
